<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60F8/8</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Czechoslovak Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hurban</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-09">July 9, 1937</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have been instructed to
                                inform Your Excellency that the Czechoslovak Government will
                                discontinue, as far as the United States is concerned, the use of
                                import certificates in connection with the export of Czechoslovak
                                rye, barley, oats, and malt to the United States.</p>
                            <p>The use of import certificates is specified in the Czechoslovak Law
                                of June 5, 1930, Number 73 of the Collection of Laws and
                                Decrees.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed>V. I. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurban</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>